 and interesting way, it also provides new insights into the conflicts that often erupt in these highly charged school spaces.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aHigh school studentszNew York (State)zNew YorkxSocial conditionsvCase studies. 0aHigh school studentszOntariozTorontoxSocial conditionsvCase studies. 0aUrban high schoolszNew York (State)zNew YorkvCase studies. 0aUrban high schoolszOntariozTorontovCase studies. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aEDUCATION / Experimental Methods.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268389140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442683891423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442683891.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK